The paper discusses a cryptographic protocol and its implementation, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The protocol involves information-theoretically secure communication, which also relates to information theory (cs.IT). The implementation involves computational capabilities, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The protocol also involves distributed computing, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the protocol involves network communication, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
